             sworn.</p>
               <p>On the 23d of November, between twelve and one, I was among the hogsheads on the keys, and I saw the prisoner taking sugar out of a barrel, the head was out, I saw him searched, and there was five pounds of sugar on him in great pockets; the sugar was under my care.</p>
               <p>PRISONER.</p>
               <p>I found it on the ground.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178212040109"></xptr>The prisoner's serjeant gave him the character of a good soldier.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17821204-82-verdict401" type="verdictDescription">
